<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="416" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1462,2030]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1678,1705]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Anterolateral margin of pronotum with solid black stripe reaching all its extension. Cicatrices with dark brown punctures delimiting anterior sulci (
<figureCitation box="[680,783,1715,1741]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="35.[151,250,1983,2008]" captionTargetBox="[250,1354,187,1936]" captionTargetId="figure@35.[190,1398,181,1957]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 19. Dorsal and ventral view. H. offuscatus A–B; H. trabeculus C–D; H. triangularis E–F; H. capito G–H; H. subrastratus I–J; H. oxyacanthus K–L (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677907" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677907/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">Fig. 19A</figureCitation>
). Anterolateral margin with few dark punctures. Male (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1746,1771]" captionTargetBox="[169,1410,207,1693]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,181,1721]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 7. H. offuscatus. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates. E—metasternal process (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677883" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677883/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
A–C). Pygophore with dorsal rim widely excavated (
<figureCitation box="[759,849,1751,1777]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1746,1771]" captionTargetBox="[169,1410,207,1693]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,181,1721]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 7. H. offuscatus. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates. E—metasternal process (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677883" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677883/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
). Superior process of genital cup small, arrow-headshaped, adjacent to dorsal rim (
<figureCitation box="[501,590,1787,1814]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1746,1771]" captionTargetBox="[169,1410,207,1693]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,181,1721]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 7. H. offuscatus. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates. E—metasternal process (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677883" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677883/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
). Paramere elongated, shank triangular (cross section) due to a conspicuous carina on inner side ending before enlarged part; head of the paramere spatulate (
<figureCitation box="[1053,1141,1823,1850]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1746,1771]" captionTargetBox="[169,1410,207,1693]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,181,1721]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 7. H. offuscatus. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates. E—metasternal process (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677883" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677883/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
). Proctiger with laterodorsal tufts of setae widely separated by medial ridge; posterior face pentagonal, flat (
<figureCitation box="[1065,1153,1859,1886]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1746,1771]" captionTargetBox="[169,1410,207,1693]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,181,1721]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 7. H. offuscatus. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates. E—metasternal process (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677883" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677883/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim with expansions rounded, wide, tumid, well-projected, clearly surpassing level of posterolateral angle in ventral view (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1746,1771]" captionTargetBox="[169,1410,207,1693]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,181,1721]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 7. H. offuscatus. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates. E—metasternal process (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677883" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677883/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">Fig. 7C</figureCitation>
); base of each expansion with a conspicuous transverse carina. Female (
<figureCitation box="[999,1090,1931,1958]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1746,1771]" captionTargetBox="[169,1410,207,1693]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,181,1721]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 7. H. offuscatus. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates. E—metasternal process (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677883" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677883/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">Fig. 7D</figureCitation>
). Gonocoxites 8 with posterior margin sinuous, inner angle rounded projected posteriorly reaching gonocoxites 9; sutural border with elliptic, short excavation on posterior half. Gonapophyses 8 exposed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
