<subSubSection lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="418" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1852,2024]" lastBlockId="17.[151,1436,152,287]" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="418" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1852,1879]" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1907" box="[342,530,1853,1879]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Edessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="offuscata">
<emphasis box="[342,530,1853,1879]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">Edessa offuscata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1907" box="[583,689,1854,1880]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Edessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rimata">
<emphasis box="[583,600,1854,1879]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[614,689,1854,1879]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">rimata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Breddin, G." box="[904,1078,1853,1879]" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" pagination="327 - 348" refId="ref24495" refString="Breddin, G. (1907) Beitrage zur Systematik der Pentatomiden Sudamerikas. Sitzungs-Berichte der Gesellschaft naturforschender freunde zu Berlin, 10, 327 - 348." type="journal article" year="1907">Breddin (1907)</bibRefCitation>
. The author considered 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1907" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Edessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rimata">
<emphasis box="[1343,1360,1854,1879]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">rimata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1907" box="[295,434,1889,1916]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Edessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trabecula">
<emphasis box="[295,312,1890,1915]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[327,434,1889,1915]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">trabecula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1907" box="[491,626,1889,1916]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Edessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="offuscata">
<emphasis box="[491,508,1890,1915]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[523,626,1889,1915]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">offuscata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
close to 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Amyot &amp; Serville" authorityYear="1843" box="[729,887,1889,1916]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadridens">
<emphasis box="[729,746,1890,1915]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[761,887,1889,1915]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">quadridens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Campos &amp; Mendonca &amp; Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Breddin" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[944,1072,1889,1916]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boerneri">
<emphasis box="[944,961,1890,1915]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[976,1072,1889,1915]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">boerneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, these similarities are based only on the external morphology of the species. Females of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Campos &amp; Mendonca &amp; Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Breddin" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[892,1040,1925,1951]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="offuscatus">
<emphasis box="[892,1040,1925,1951]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">H. offuscatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have inner angles of gonocoxites 8 more protruding and sutural border less excavated (
<figureCitation box="[724,811,1961,1988]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1746,1771]" captionTargetBox="[169,1410,207,1693]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,181,1721]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 7. H. offuscatus. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates. E—metasternal process (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677883" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677883/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">Fig. 7D</figureCitation>
) than 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Campos &amp; Mendonca &amp; Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Breddin" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[880,1009,1961,1987]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boerneri">
<emphasis box="[880,1009,1961,1987]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">H. boerneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1025,1114,1961,1987]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1805,1830]" captionTargetBox="[171,1421,437,1746]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,417,1780]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2. H. boerneri. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates. E—metasternal process (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677873" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677873/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
); both species have posterior margin of gonocoxites 8 sinuous while 
<emphasis box="[586,750,1996,2024]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">
<taxonomicName box="[586,739,1996,2024]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadriden">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[586,739,1996,2024]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">H. quadriden</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s
</emphasis>
has posterior margin arched (
<figureCitation box="[1078,1166,1997,2023]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1912,1937]" captionTargetBox="[225,1364,199,1866]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[214,1374,179,1884]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 1. H. quadridens. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B–posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates. E—metasternal process; F—Habitus, Lectotype male; G—specimen data. (pyg—pygophore; dr—dorsal rim; vr—ventral rim; proc—proctiger; gp—genital superior process; pa—parameres; gc8—gonocoxite 8; gc9—gonocoxites 9; la8—laterotergite 8; la9—laterotergite 9; x—abdominal segment X. Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677871" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677871/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
). Males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Campos &amp; Mendonca &amp; Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Breddin" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[1290,1437,1997,2023]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="offuscatus">
<emphasis box="[1290,1437,1997,2023]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">H. offuscatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[200,367,152,179]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">
<taxonomicName box="[200,355,152,179]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadriden">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[200,355,152,179]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">H. quadriden</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s
</emphasis>
are very similar and can be separated by subtle characteristics like paramere more robust and dorsal rim more excavated in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Campos &amp; Mendonca &amp; Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Breddin" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[487,636,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="offuscatus">
<emphasis box="[487,636,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">H. offuscatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[652,737,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1746,1771]" captionTargetBox="[169,1410,207,1693]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,181,1721]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 7. H. offuscatus. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates. E—metasternal process (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677883" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677883/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[793,827,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1912,1937]" captionTargetBox="[225,1364,199,1866]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[214,1374,179,1884]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 1. H. quadridens. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B–posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates. E—metasternal process; F—Habitus, Lectotype male; G—specimen data. (pyg—pygophore; dr—dorsal rim; vr—ventral rim; proc—proctiger; gp—genital superior process; pa—parameres; gc8—gonocoxite 8; gc9—gonocoxites 9; la8—laterotergite 8; la9—laterotergite 9; x—abdominal segment X. Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677871" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677871/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">1B</figureCitation>
); more obvious distinctive characteristic is the expansion of ventral rim more developed and rounded in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Campos &amp; Mendonca &amp; Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Breddin" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[727,876,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="offuscatus">
<emphasis box="[727,876,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">H. offuscatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[890,977,225,251]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1746,1771]" captionTargetBox="[169,1410,207,1693]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,181,1721]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 7. H. offuscatus. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates. E—metasternal process (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677883" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677883/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">Fig. 7C</figureCitation>
) than in 
<emphasis box="[1076,1241,224,251]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">
<taxonomicName box="[1076,1230,224,251]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadriden">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1076,1230,224,251]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">H. quadriden</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1256,1343,225,251]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1912,1937]" captionTargetBox="[225,1364,199,1866]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[214,1374,179,1884]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 1. H. quadridens. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B–posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates. E—metasternal process; F—Habitus, Lectotype male; G—specimen data. (pyg—pygophore; dr—dorsal rim; vr—ventral rim; proc—proctiger; gp—genital superior process; pa—parameres; gc8—gonocoxite 8; gc9—gonocoxites 9; la8—laterotergite 8; la9—laterotergite 9; x—abdominal segment X. Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677871" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677871/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
